<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extracts.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Pike</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 224.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Hague,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-09"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 9, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 15th of February, No. 142.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>The Jews have taken to buying our bonds largely, as they get them at a
                                <pb facs="0331" n="311" xml:id="pg_311"/> rate which pays them near
                            10 per cent. for their money. I am told the transactions at Amsterdam
                            amount to near two millions weekly.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with great respect, your most obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>JAMES S. PIKE.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>